    <node id="AIDA">
      <data key="d0">AIDA</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">AIDA is a well-established marketing formula that serves as a guiding framework for content creation and consumer engagement. The acronym AIDA stands for Attention, Interest, Desire, and Action, representing the sequential stages that potential customers typically progress through during the buying process.

The model emphasizes the importance of capturing the customer’s Attention first, which is crucial for initiating the sales process. Once attention is gained, the next step is to stimulate Interest by providing information that appeals to the consumer's needs or desires. Following Interest, the formula seeks to create Desire, encouraging potential buyers to want the product or service being offered. Finally, AIDA culminates in the Action stage, where the goal is to convert the consumer's interest and desire into a purchase or other desired behavior.

AIDA is widely recognized and used in various forms of marketing and advertising to effectively guide strategies aimed at engaging target audiences. It is classified as a secondary marketing formula, underscoring its role as a key tool in shaping effective marketing campaigns and enhancing sales processes through structured consumer behavior analysis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3a204592fbffe6cfeb6984f733bccc40&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-14aa9b8a6928b34255ea52ee4c3b45d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a74983159b5d9d60562b14b3efe79ed4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3dbdb4018965a35bc831c46b628ef1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-310c209905e34b3117ff6c7a1bca1f83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-329eaee1aec1b601d88beada37d0d6f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8f2b43caa2d3405de1738e3b7ba665f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f0d06ee8de6aad13c1a75678a4a0bed</data>
