    <node id="Golden Hour">
      <data key="d0">Golden Hour</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Golden Hour refers to the first 60 minutes after posting content, which significantly influences the post's overall reach by maximizing early engagement.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ad567cc337e56f77d96c7671a22f0986</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:engagement-triggers:golden-hour</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002559</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Engagement Velocity">
      <data key="d0">Engagement Velocity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Engagement velocity indicates the rate of interactions a post receives shortly after publishing and is a key factor in how content is distributed on platforms.&lt;SEP&gt;Engagement velocity refers to the rate at which interactions occur on a post, impacting its reach and visibility on Facebook.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ad567cc337e56f77d96c7671a22f0986&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:engagement-triggers:golden-hour&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002806</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Analytics Tab">
      <data key="d0">Analytics Tab</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The analytics tab is a tool provided by platforms to help users determine the most active times of their audience, aiding in optimal posting strategies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ad567cc337e56f77d96c7671a22f0986</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:engagement-triggers:golden-hour</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002559</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Post Boosting">
      <data key="d0">Post Boosting</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Post boosting involves actions like pinning posts and responding promptly to comments to increase visibility and engagement within the critical first hour after posting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ad567cc337e56f77d96c7671a22f0986</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:engagement-triggers:golden-hour</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002559</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Audience">
      <data key="d0">Audience</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Audience refers to the group of individuals who engage with posts on social media, whose active times are crucial for maximizing engagement during the Golden Hour.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ad567cc337e56f77d96c7671a22f0986</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:engagement-triggers:golden-hour</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002559</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Comments">
      <data key="d0">Comments</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Comments are responses from the audience that can signal activity to the ranker and should be replied to promptly within the first 30 minutes.&lt;SEP&gt;Comments are user interactions where viewers express their thoughts, particularly valuable when they generate threads of replies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ad567cc337e56f77d96c7671a22f0986&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:engagement-triggers:golden-hour&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Style">
      <data key="d0">Branded Style</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Style refers to the default style for everyday posts when neither creative nor marketing styles are appropriate.&lt;SEP&gt;Branded Style is a marketing style used for educational or engaging posts, emphasizing brand identity and storytelling without direct calls to action.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tip / Advice Posts">
      <data key="d0">Tip / Advice Posts</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Tip / Advice Posts are a type of content that provides helpful information, typically framed as "3 things you should know about X."</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002572</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="News / Updates / Announcements">
      <data key="d0">News / Updates / Announcements</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">News / Updates / Announcements refer to non-promotional content that informs the audience about current events or updates.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002572</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Storytelling Posts">
      <data key="d0">Storytelling Posts</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Storytelling Posts are designed to engage the audience with narratives that include a hook to capture interest.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002572</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Industry Insights">
      <data key="d0">Industry Insights</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Industry Insights provide valuable information and opinions about a specific industry, aiding audience understanding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002572</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Engagement-Bait Questions">
      <data key="d0">Engagement-Bait Questions</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Engagement-Bait Questions are provocative questions designed to generate audience interaction, usually paired with visuals.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002572</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Creative Style">
      <data key="d0">Creative Style</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Creative Style is used for behind-the-scenes mood pieces that aim to express a feeling or atmosphere rather than a message.&lt;SEP&gt;Creative Style is a writing approach focused on evoking emotional connections and brand vibes rather than direct conversion or education.&lt;SEP&gt;Creative Style is a marketing approach focusing on mood and lifestyle, suitable for campaigns not aimed at direct sales.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002709</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Style">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Style</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Style is employed for promotional content, including discount announcements, product launches, or limited-time offers.&lt;SEP&gt;Marketing Style is a writing approach focused on product promotion, feature claims, tips, or sales announcements.&lt;SEP&gt;Marketing Style refers to a specific approach used for posts aimed at achieving commercial goals, ensuring the content effectively communicates a message.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Posts">
      <data key="d0">Posts</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Posts refer to various types of content shared on platforms, including advice, news, storytelling, and engagement posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002573</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Visuals">
      <data key="d0">Visuals</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Visuals refer to images or graphics that accompany posts to enhance engagement and draw the audience's attention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5de24af04a6e5aa3cc721697b9b37edc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:when-to-use-branded-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002573</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Composition Rules">
      <data key="d0">Branded Composition Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Composition Rules refer to guidelines for creating visually appealing images that prioritize photographic composition and branding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-007a665f6654a78bca0fd2f1f27d50b2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002583</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hero Subject">
      <data key="d0">Hero Subject</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Hero Subject is a prominent element in a composition, intended to attract the viewer's attention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-007a665f6654a78bca0fd2f1f27d50b2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002583</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Headline-Safe Area">
      <data key="d0">Headline-Safe Area</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Headline-Safe Area is the portion of an image where text can be placed without disrupting the visual composition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-007a665f6654a78bca0fd2f1f27d50b2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002583</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rule of Thirds">
      <data key="d0">Rule of Thirds</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Rule of Thirds is a compositional guideline that suggests dividing an image into thirds both horizontally and vertically, positioning key elements along these lines.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule of Thirds is a compositional technique where the subject is positioned at a one-third intersection rather than being centered.&lt;SEP&gt;The Rule of Thirds is a photography and composition technique that involves dividing the frame into a 3x3 grid to enhance visual appeal.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-007a665f6654a78bca0fd2f1f27d50b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a184060d44406503c4befead6608fca</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:visual-design:rule-of-thirds</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003047</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Aspect Ratio">
      <data key="d0">Aspect Ratio</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Aspect Ratio defines the proportional relationship between an image's width and height, with specified ratios for various formats.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspect Ratio defines the proportions of an image, with specifications for different formats including 1:1, 4:5, 9:16, and marketing-style 16:9.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspect ratio specifies the proportional relationship between width and height of visual elements in marketing designs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-007a665f6654a78bca0fd2f1f27d50b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mobile-First">
      <data key="d0">Mobile-First</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Mobile-First is a design philosophy that prioritizes the mobile user experience, ensuring that subjects are recognizable even at smaller dimensions.&lt;SEP&gt;Mobile-first approach emphasizes designing marketing materials primarily for mobile devices before considering desktop formats.&lt;SEP&gt;Mobile-First refers to the design principle emphasizing the use of a vertical 9:16 aspect ratio for short-form videos on various platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-007a665f6654a78bca0fd2f1f27d50b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c676dbaddd0ab5a88338a4bf4ae4f4c9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:visual-design:mobile-first-9-16</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Text Rules">
      <data key="d0">Branded Text Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Text Rules outlines guidelines for creating effective branded text, including rules for headlines, subheads, and formatting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002593</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Headline">
      <data key="d0">Headline</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A Headline should be a short phrase of 3–8 words that grabs attention.&lt;SEP&gt;Headline is a prominent element in marketing composition, designed to convey the value proposition in 3–6 words.&lt;SEP&gt;Headline is a mandatory element that must contain 3-6 words, showing the value proposition or offer, and following specific design requirements.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05adc5964c57d4756f5f71a57d0ebe78</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002735</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Subhead">
      <data key="d0">Subhead</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A Subhead is an optional short phrase of 4–10 words that provides context to the headline.&lt;SEP&gt;Subhead is an optional element consisting of 4-10 words that provides detail or qualifiers about the offer, with its own design specifications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05adc5964c57d4756f5f71a57d0ebe78</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002735</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Body Copy">
      <data key="d0">Body Copy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Body Copy refers to the main text area, which is not allowed in branded text rules.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002593</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="CTA Buttons">
      <data key="d0">CTA Buttons</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CTA Buttons are marketing calls to action that are prohibited in branded text.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002593</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Contact Info">
      <data key="d0">Contact Info</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Contact Info must be placed in the caption and cannot appear in the branded text.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002593</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Type Hierarchy">
      <data key="d0">Type Hierarchy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type Hierarchy outlines the font size and alignment rules for headlines and subheads in branded text.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002593</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Contrast">
      <data key="d0">Contrast</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Contrast requirements state that text must meet WCAG AA standards against its background color.&lt;SEP&gt;Contrast involves ensuring that text color strongly contrasts with the background, sometimes utilizing a semi-transparent box for visibility.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b5981bf8a153ad8ee40e4b54bc70f435&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-text-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Brand Presence">
      <data key="d0">Branded Brand Presence</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Brand Presence refers to the visibility of a brand mark that does not dominate the overall design.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2143f392f169f3b590cc0dd33b9ebfda</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002603</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Wordmark or Logo">
      <data key="d0">Wordmark or Logo</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">A Wordmark or Logo is a visual representation of the brand that can be placed in a corner of an image.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2143f392f169f3b590cc0dd33b9ebfda</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002603</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Color Accent">
      <data key="d0">Brand Color Accent</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand Color Accent involves using brand colors within a design to reinforce brand identity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2143f392f169f3b590cc0dd33b9ebfda</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002603</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tagline Lockup">
      <data key="d0">Tagline Lockup</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tagline Lockup refers to the presentation of taglines alongside brand marks, which is suggested to be omitted.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2143f392f169f3b590cc0dd33b9ebfda</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002603</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Handle">
      <data key="d0">Handle</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Handle pertains to social media identifiers that should not be displayed as a promotional element in branding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2143f392f169f3b590cc0dd33b9ebfda</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002603</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Consistency Check">
      <data key="d0">Brand Consistency Check</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand Consistency Check refers to evaluating whether an image is recognizable as a brand within 500 milliseconds, without reading any text.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2143f392f169f3b590cc0dd33b9ebfda</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002603</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Color &amp; Lighting">
      <data key="d0">Branded Color &amp; Lighting</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Color &amp; Lighting refers to the visual elements, including color palettes and lighting that reflect brand identity in posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-20dd2eeadb182ea661fb96db38ceefbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-color-lighting</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002616</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Palette">
      <data key="d0">Palette</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Palette refers to the selection of colors derived from brand identity to ensure consistency in visual representation.&lt;SEP&gt;A palette is determined by brand identity and influences the visual presentation of posts based on previous content.&lt;SEP&gt;Palette refers to the selection of brand colors that should be visible in brand presentations but not as labels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-20dd2eeadb182ea661fb96db38ceefbc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05c801375004ec513d4e8096533dc185</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-color-lighting&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002690</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Headline Color">
      <data key="d0">Headline Color</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Headline Color is the color choice for text that needs to maintain maximum readability against various backgrounds.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-20dd2eeadb182ea661fb96db38ceefbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-color-lighting</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002616</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Background">
      <data key="d0">Background</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Background refers to the visual foundation of a post, which can include photos, illustrations, or solid brand colors.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-20dd2eeadb182ea661fb96db38ceefbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-color-lighting</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002616</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Post">
      <data key="d0">Branded Post</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Post refers to social media posts that utilize specific colors and lighting to align with the brand's identity and visual strategy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-20dd2eeadb182ea661fb96db38ceefbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-color-lighting</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002616</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lighting">
      <data key="d0">Lighting</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-20dd2eeadb182ea661fb96db38ceefbc</data>
      <data key="d2">Palette choices should consider the Lighting to match the brand's typical mood for better visual harmony.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-color-lighting</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002618</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Branded Layout Patterns">
      <data key="d0">Branded Layout Patterns</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Branded Layout Patterns refer to three distinct visual strategies that enhance the effectiveness of branded posts, each serving specific content types.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-19ff6b4cd2b981c4e299f73f1969442a</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-layout-patterns</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pattern A">
      <data key="d0">Pattern A</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Pattern A is a layout pattern for branded posts that incorporates a brand color or white block for the headline, alongside a hero photo and is suitable for tip posts and news.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-19ff6b4cd2b981c4e299f73f1969442a</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-layout-patterns</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pattern B">
      <data key="d0">Pattern B</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Pattern B features a layout where the top two-thirds consist of a hero photo and the bottom third includes a brand color block with a headline and subhead, ideal for storytelling and lifestyle posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-19ff6b4cd2b981c4e299f73f1969442a</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-layout-patterns</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pattern C">
      <data key="d0">Pattern C</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Pattern C involves a full-bleed photo with a subtle dark gradient and places the headline over the gradient area, best suited for editorial-feel posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-19ff6b4cd2b981c4e299f73f1969442a</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-branded:branded-layout-patterns</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002627</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Behind-the-Scenes Glimpses">
      <data key="d0">Behind-the-Scenes Glimpses</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Behind-the-Scenes Glimpses involve showcasing internal team moments and storytelling to create a personal connection with the audience.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002640</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lifestyle Imagery">
      <data key="d0">Lifestyle Imagery</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Lifestyle Imagery refers to visual content that inspires and aspirates by aligning with a brand's values and aesthetics.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002640</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Vibe Posts">
      <data key="d0">Brand Vibe Posts</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand Vibe Posts are shared to convey the essence and mood of a brand without promoting specific products.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002640</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Photography-Led Brands">
      <data key="d0">Photography-Led Brands</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Photography-Led Brands are brands in sectors like food, fashion, travel, and fitness that depend heavily on visual content to engage audiences.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002640</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Trending-Format Participation">
      <data key="d0">Trending-Format Participation</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Trending-Format Participation includes engaging with popular formats such as memes or cultural moments to connect with audiences dynamically.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-68ba12ae5ff3f0aecb6e23aa8381dd83</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:when-to-use-creative-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002640</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Creative Composition Rules">
      <data key="d0">Creative Composition Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Creative Composition Rules encompass guidelines for creating visually compelling photographic compositions focused on atmosphere and structure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002653</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Single Hero Subject">
      <data key="d0">Single Hero Subject</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Single Hero Subject refers to the practice of using one clear focal point in an image to avoid cluttered layouts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002653</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Negative Space">
      <data key="d0">Negative Space</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Negative Space is the technique of allowing the subject room to breathe in the composition without cluttering every pixel.&lt;SEP&gt;Negative Space refers to a design principle that emphasizes allowing space around subjects to enhance clarity and impact.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4b610e2de93502f15a042b434c8e53de</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:visual-design:negative-space</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003180</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cinematic Framing">
      <data key="d0">Cinematic Framing</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Cinematic Framing involves using shallow depth of field, leading lines, and layered foreground/background to enhance visual interest.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002653</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Natural Lighting">
      <data key="d0">Natural Lighting</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Natural Lighting refers to utilizing soft, diffused lighting, such as golden hour or window light, while avoiding harsh overhead lighting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f221ba7743d1dca6e150702038ffe4cc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002653</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Creative Text Rules">
      <data key="d0">Creative Text Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Creative Text Rules are guidelines for creating readable images without incorporating text elements, emphasizing design over marketing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c22796214eab5ad0c81668abff16d0e9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002667</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Artistic Typography">
      <data key="d0">Artistic Typography</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Artistic Typography refers to a single short word or phrase used in images, treated as a design element rather than a marketing claim.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c22796214eab5ad0c81668abff16d0e9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002667</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing">
      <data key="d0">Marketing</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing encompasses strategies that include headline + body + CTA stacks, which are restricted in the context of the creative text rules.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c22796214eab5ad0c81668abff16d0e9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002667</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Text Constraint">
      <data key="d0">Text Constraint</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Text Constraint refers to the requirement that any text on an image is considered a constraint rather than a feature in creative design.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c22796214eab5ad0c81668abff16d0e9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002667</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Image Content">
      <data key="d0">Image Content</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Image Content includes the visual aspects of an image that must remain free from marketing text, emphasizing readability.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c22796214eab5ad0c81668abff16d0e9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002667</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Creative Color &amp; Mood">
      <data key="d0">Creative Color &amp; Mood</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Creative Color &amp; Mood refers to the concepts of color palettes and their meanings in relation to brand identities and the mood they convey.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002679</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="RAG'd Reference Images">
      <data key="d0">RAG'd Reference Images</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">RAG'd reference images are used to establish a color palette derived from past posts for consistency in branding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002679</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Warm Tones">
      <data key="d0">Warm Tones</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Warm tones include colors like golden and amber, associated with moods like coziness, nostalgia, food, and lifestyle.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002679</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cool Tones">
      <data key="d0">Cool Tones</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cool tones, such as blue, teal, and slate, are linked to moods of technology, premium quality, and trustworthiness.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002680</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High Saturation">
      <data key="d0">High Saturation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">High saturation colors are vibrant and are associated with energetic, youthful, and bold feelings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002680</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Desaturated / Muted">
      <data key="d0">Desaturated / Muted</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Desaturated or muted colors convey editorial, timeless, and premium aesthetics.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002680</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Mood">
      <data key="d0">Brand Mood</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand mood relates to the emotional tone conveyed by a brand's visual identity, which should be consistent with the brand's profile and offerings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002680</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Wellness Brand">
      <data key="d0">Wellness Brand</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A wellness brand focuses on health and well-being, requiring a calm and appropriate color palette in its branding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002680</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tech Brand">
      <data key="d0">Tech Brand</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A tech brand is associated with technological innovation and quality, necessitating a color palette that reflects a premium and trustworthy image.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b0d7722e8fcfa82a6ba972838b0d9ea</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-color-mood</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002680</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Creative Brand Presence">
      <data key="d0">Creative Brand Presence</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Creative Brand Presence refers to the idea that a brand's essence is perceived through its visual style rather than overt displays like logos.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05c801375004ec513d4e8096533dc185</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002690</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand">
      <data key="d0">Brand</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand represents the identity and perception of a product or service, which should be recognizable through visual elements.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05c801375004ec513d4e8096533dc185</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002690</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Visual Style">
      <data key="d0">Visual Style</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Visual Style encompasses the aesthetic characteristics utilized by a brand to convey its identity without relying on logos.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05c801375004ec513d4e8096533dc185</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002690</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Signature Elements">
      <data key="d0">Signature Elements</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Signature Elements are unique characteristics of a brand, including recurring props, specific filters, or artistic typography used for branding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05c801375004ec513d4e8096533dc185</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002690</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Patterns">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Patterns</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Patterns refer to conventional promotional features such as frames, badges, or banners that should be avoided in creative brand presentations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05c801375004ec513d4e8096533dc185</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-creative:creative-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002690</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sales/Discounts">
      <data key="d0">Sales/Discounts</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">Sales/Discounts refer to promotions designed to reduce prices and encourage customer purchases within a set time frame.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Service Offerings">
      <data key="d0">Service Offerings</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Service Offerings are features or benefits provided to customers, often promoted through advertising to attract clients.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Event Announcements">
      <data key="d0">Event Announcements</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Event Announcements pertain to notifications about upcoming events, which include details such as date, venue, and RSVP information.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lead Magnets">
      <data key="d0">Lead Magnets</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lead Magnets are marketing tools designed to attract potential customers by offering free valuable items or services in exchange for contact information.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="B2B Service Ads">
      <data key="d0">B2B Service Ads</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">B2B Service Ads are advertisements targeting business-to-business transactions, emphasizing service offerings for other businesses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Direct-Response Posts">
      <data key="d0">Direct-Response Posts</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Direct-Response Posts are marketing messages intended to provoke immediate responses from the audience, typically measured by actions like clicks or replies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8fde58ed6d6a1555100e83cef72d633d</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:when-to-use-marketing-style</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002708</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Composition Rules">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Composition Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Composition Rules outline guidelines for creating layouts that facilitate fast comprehension for viewers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F-Pattern Reading Order">
      <data key="d0">F-Pattern Reading Order</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">F-pattern reading order describes a visual reading strategy that guides viewers through content layout in a specific sequence.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Visual Hierarchy">
      <data key="d0">Visual Hierarchy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Visual hierarchy emphasizes the arrangement of elements in design to convey importance and structure of information.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hero Visual">
      <data key="d0">Hero Visual</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hero visual refers to a primary image or visual representation in marketing that communicates the product, outcome, or transformation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Supporting Copy">
      <data key="d0">Supporting Copy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Supporting copy consists of brief text lines that provide additional proof or detail beneath the headline and hero visual.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Call To Action (CTA)">
      <data key="d0">Call To Action (CTA)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Call To Action (CTA) is an interactive element designed to encourage users to take specific actions, prominently placed in marketing layouts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002723</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Safe Area">
      <data key="d0">Safe Area</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Safe area refers to the portions of the frame where critical text should be clear of UI overlays in social media formats.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bff89de66eb11452e6ac58c20aabe664</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-composition-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002724</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Text Rules">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Text Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Text Rules outline the structure and guidelines for creating effective promotional content with different text layers and hierarchy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05adc5964c57d4756f5f71a57d0ebe78</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002735</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="CTA Button">
      <data key="d0">CTA Button</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">CTA Button is a mandatory element that should contain 1-3 words, encouraging action, and must be visually styled as a button.&lt;SEP&gt;CTA Button refers to a call-to-action button which should have high contrast to effectively capture user attention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05adc5964c57d4756f5f71a57d0ebe78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-text-rules&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002776</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Contact Line">
      <data key="d0">Contact Line</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Contact Line is a mandatory component that includes the page's website and at least one contact method, formatted for clarity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05adc5964c57d4756f5f71a57d0ebe78</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002735</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Text Limit">
      <data key="d0">Total Text Limit</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Total Text Limit refers to the maximum word count of roughly 25 words allowed across various components of the marketing text, ensuring effective communication.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-05adc5964c57d4756f5f71a57d0ebe78</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-text-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002735</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Brand Presence">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Brand Presence</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Brand Presence refers to the overall visibility and recognition of a brand, encompassing its logo, name, colors, and tagline.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Logo">
      <data key="d0">Brand Logo</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">The Brand Logo is a graphic representation that includes the wordmark and is used prominently in marketing materials.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Colors">
      <data key="d0">Brand Colors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand Colors are the specific colors associated with a brand that must be consistently applied across various marketing elements.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tagline">
      <data key="d0">Tagline</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A Tagline is a short phrase (3-6 words) associated with the brand that reinforces its identity and message.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Campaign">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Campaign</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">A Marketing Campaign is a series of promotional activities aimed at establishing brand presence and consistency across different mediums.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Logo Lockup">
      <data key="d0">Brand Logo Lockup</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand Logo Lockup refers to the specific arrangement of the brand logo and wordmark used in marketing materials.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Call to Action (CTA)">
      <data key="d0">Call to Action (CTA)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Call to Action (CTA) is a marketing term referring to prompts that encourage the audience to take specific actions, typically represented visually with buttons.&lt;SEP&gt;Call to Action (CTA) is a marketing element that prompts the audience to take a specific action, such as making a purchase or signing up.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42570b285779ca83fc44089b5d4c463f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-trust-signals-optional-add-ons</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002789</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Frame Width">
      <data key="d0">Frame Width</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Frame Width relates to the proportion of the visual space that the brand logo should occupy, typically expressed as a percentage.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a39d222abd2dee960e115829bbbbd675</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-brand-presence</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002750</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Visual Anchors">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Visual Anchors</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Visual Anchors refer to visual elements in marketing that enhance the offer without distracting from it.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e56b4d29cd042b4575cf88d57c1e4b53</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-visual-anchors</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Product Shot">
      <data key="d0">Product Shot</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The Product Shot is a marketing technique involving a clean background, a single product, and good lighting without a busy lifestyle scene.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e56b4d29cd042b4575cf88d57c1e4b53</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-visual-anchors</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Before/After">
      <data key="d0">Before/After</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The Before/After method utilizes a split-frame format with clear labels to show comparative results.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e56b4d29cd042b4575cf88d57c1e4b53</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-visual-anchors</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Outcome Shot">
      <data key="d0">Outcome Shot</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The Outcome Shot involves depicting a customer using the product with a smile and maintaining eye contact with the camera to signal high trust.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e56b4d29cd042b4575cf88d57c1e4b53</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-visual-anchors</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Discount Badge / Sticker">
      <data key="d0">Discount Badge / Sticker</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The Discount Badge / Sticker is used in marketing for sales, featuring high-contrast designs such as "-50%" or "FREE" in brand colors.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e56b4d29cd042b4575cf88d57c1e4b53</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-visual-anchors</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Stock Photography">
      <data key="d0">Stock Photography</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Stock Photography is an approach that should be avoided if it does not feature the actual product or service.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e56b4d29cd042b4575cf88d57c1e4b53</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-visual-anchors</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Color &amp; Contrast">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Color &amp; Contrast</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Color &amp; Contrast refers to the principles of using color and contrast to maximize engagement and clicks in marketing materials.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002776</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High Contrast">
      <data key="d0">High Contrast</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">High Contrast emphasizes the importance of using stark differences in color to draw attention and increase click rates.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002776</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="WCAG AAA">
      <data key="d0">WCAG AAA</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">WCAG AAA is a standard that specifies minimum contrast ratios of 7:1 for text-to-background to ensure readability.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002776</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Brand Color Discipline">
      <data key="d0">Brand Color Discipline</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Brand Color Discipline outlines the guidelines for using brand colors effectively while allowing for variations that enhance contrast.&lt;SEP&gt;Brand Color Discipline refers to the strategy of using a limited color palette in branding to build recognition and visual consistency across posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fea7d7f065b62f47a9e8d0484fe5cae</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:visual-design:brand-color-discipline</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003120</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pastel Palettes">
      <data key="d0">Pastel Palettes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pastel Palettes consist of soft colors that are typically used in creative branding but should be avoided in marketing headlines.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002776</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Color Contrast">
      <data key="d0">Color Contrast</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Color Contrast refers to the difference in color that makes text or elements stand out against their background, crucial for marketing effectiveness.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-11a6649b61c186427fcd108409f7c6f2</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-color-contrast</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002776</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marketing Trust Signals">
      <data key="d0">Marketing Trust Signals</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Marketing Trust Signals refers to optional add-ons that enhance credibility in marketing posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42570b285779ca83fc44089b5d4c463f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-trust-signals-optional-add-ons</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002789</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Social Proof">
      <data key="d0">Social Proof</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Social Proof is a trust signal indicating credibility through customer reviews and ratings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42570b285779ca83fc44089b5d4c463f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-trust-signals-optional-add-ons</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002789</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Scarcity">
      <data key="d0">Scarcity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Scarcity is a trust signal that creates urgency by indicating limited availability of a product.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42570b285779ca83fc44089b5d4c463f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-trust-signals-optional-add-ons</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002789</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Guarantee">
      <data key="d0">Guarantee</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Guarantee is a trust signal offering assurance to customers, such as a money-back promise.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42570b285779ca83fc44089b5d4c463f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-trust-signals-optional-add-ons</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002789</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Authority">
      <data key="d0">Authority</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Authority is a trust signal that establishes credibility through endorsements from recognized publications or influencers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42570b285779ca83fc44089b5d4c463f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:image-design-marketing:marketing-trust-signals-optional-add-ons</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002789</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Meaningful Interactions">
      <data key="d0">Meaningful Interactions</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Meaningful interactions refer to comments and replies that are prioritized over likes on Facebook, affecting engagement and content reach.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002806</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="FB Reels">
      <data key="d0">FB Reels</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">FB Reels are short video segments on Facebook where watch-completion rates and replays play a crucial role in determining distribution.&lt;SEP&gt;FB Reels refers to Facebook's short video feature that allows users to create and share vertical videos.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c676dbaddd0ab5a88338a4bf4ae4f4c9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:visual-design:mobile-first-9-16</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Group Posts">
      <data key="d0">Group Posts</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Group posts refer to content shared within active groups on Facebook that may achieve higher organic reach compared to page posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002806</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Organic Reach">
      <data key="d0">Organic Reach</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Organic reach is the number of unique users who see a page's content without paid promotions, which can vary based on interaction levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002806</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Recency">
      <data key="d0">Recency</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Recency is a factor in Facebook's algorithm where newer content is more likely to be favored in user feeds.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002806</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tactical Takeaways">
      <data key="d0">Tactical Takeaways</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tactical takeaways include specific strategies for improving engagement on posts, such as ending with a question and uploading videos natively.&lt;SEP&gt;Tactical takeaways include content strategies for maximizing engagement and reach on Instagram.&lt;SEP&gt;Tactical takeaways include strategies for creating effective TikTok videos, such as keeping them short and engaging from the start.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2f1e58b563431de779523f5c6b88ac3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:facebook&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Saves">
      <data key="d0">Saves</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Saves are considered the strongest signal in Instagram's feed algorithm for determining content ranking.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002823</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Shares">
      <data key="d0">Shares</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Shares, which include direct messages and stories, represent the second-strongest signal for Instagram's content ranking.&lt;SEP&gt;Shares represent the action of users sharing videos both within the TikTok platform and to other social media platforms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Stories">
      <data key="d0">Stories</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Stories are temporary posts on Instagram where reply rates serve as a dominant engagement signal.&lt;SEP&gt;Stories are short-lived video or photo content designed to captivate viewers quickly on social media.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ddb34470f164e1f8baeb7a56a0e0b6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram&lt;SEP&gt;knowledge:viral-hooks:3-second-rule</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002909</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Account-Level Signals">
      <data key="d0">Account-Level Signals</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Account-level signals consider a user's past post performance over 90 days, affecting new post ranking based on quality score.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002823</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Account Quality Score">
      <data key="d0">Account Quality Score</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Account Quality Score is a measure that influences the ranking of new posts based on past performance within the Instagram algorithm.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002823</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hashtags">
      <data key="d0">Hashtags</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hashtags are keywords preceded by "#" that are used to categorize content on Instagram, with a cap of 30 per post, though fewer hashtags correlate with higher reach.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-099fa493d309316ed02f5deace628766</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:instagram</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002824</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Completion Rate">
      <data key="d0">Completion Rate</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Completion rate is the percentage of viewers who watched a video to the end, considered the most important signal on TikTok.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rewatches">
      <data key="d0">Rewatches</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Rewatches refer to the number of times viewers watch the same short video, contributing to total watch time.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Velocity in First Hour">
      <data key="d0">Velocity in First Hour</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Velocity in the first hour indicates how quickly a video gains views and likes, influencing its distribution on TikTok.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Banned Audio/Music">
      <data key="d0">Banned Audio/Music</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Banned audio or music refers to copyrighted material that TikTok actively removes from videos, impacting video reach.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002843</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Watermarks">
      <data key="d0">Watermarks</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Watermarks, such as those from Instagram and YouTube, are logos that TikTok suppresses when they appear on cross-posted content.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002844</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Long Videos">
      <data key="d0">Long Videos</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Long videos are those exceeding 3 minutes, which TikTok penalizes if they do not achieve high completion rates.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002844</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Trending Audio">
      <data key="d0">Trending Audio</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Trending audio refers to popular music or sound clips that can boost the initial reach of TikTok videos when used.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-727ef4898851d6e16f17c75a77ba39d9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:tiktok</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002844</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reply-Rate">
      <data key="d0">Reply-Rate</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reply-rate is the primary engagement signal on Threads, measuring how many viewers respond to a post compared to just liking it.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Quote-Replies">
      <data key="d0">Quote-Replies</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Quote-replies amplify posts by sharing them with a user's followers, making it the highest-leverage engagement type.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reply-Thread Depth">
      <data key="d0">Reply-Thread Depth</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reply-thread depth refers to the chain of replies that generate additional responses, increasing overall impressions on Threads.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Trending-Topic Association">
      <data key="d0">Trending-Topic Association</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Trending-topic association involves mentioning currently trending subjects, providing a temporary boost to post visibility.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Account Follow Growth">
      <data key="d0">Account Follow Growth</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Account follow growth signals the quality of content based on the number of new followers gained from individual posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Negative Engagement">
      <data key="d0">Negative Engagement</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Negative engagement is characterized by mass mutes or blocks, which negatively affect the visibility and ranking of posts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Self-Promotion">
      <data key="d0">Self-Promotion</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Self-promotion refers to promoting oneself or one's content without providing substantial value, often seen as a negative practice on Threads.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002864</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reposts of Twitter/X Content">
      <data key="d0">Reposts of Twitter/X Content</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reposts of Twitter/X content are instances of sharing content from Twitter/X, which Threads suppresses to maintain originality.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002865</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Long Monologues">
      <data key="d0">Long Monologues</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Long monologues are lengthy posts that lack engagement hooks, which tend to underperform compared to shorter posts with questions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a32f52be8fde29e94ed58c180a24ce6</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:threads</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002865</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="YouTube">
      <data key="d0">YouTube</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">YouTube is a video-sharing platform that utilizes various metrics to rank and recommend videos to users.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-06ab9774b6e9aa0aeab7a13fdb038dbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:youtube-for-future-expansion</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002889</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Click-Through Rate (CTR)">
      <data key="d0">Click-Through Rate (CTR)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Click-Through Rate (CTR) measures the effectiveness of a thumbnail and title combination in earning viewer clicks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-06ab9774b6e9aa0aeab7a13fdb038dbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:youtube-for-future-expansion</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002889</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Average View Duration">
      <data key="d0">Average View Duration</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Average View Duration refers to the total watch minutes that content receives, serving as important currency for video ranking.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-06ab9774b6e9aa0aeab7a13fdb038dbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:youtube-for-future-expansion</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002889</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="First-30-Second Retention">
      <data key="d0">First-30-Second Retention</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">First-30-Second Retention indicates viewer retention within the first 30 seconds of a video, impacting its recommendation likelihood.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-06ab9774b6e9aa0aeab7a13fdb038dbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:youtube-for-future-expansion</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002889</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Session Time">
      <data key="d0">Session Time</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Session Time measures how videos lead viewers to watch additional content on YouTube, which can enhance ranking signals.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-06ab9774b6e9aa0aeab7a13fdb038dbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:youtube-for-future-expansion</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002889</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Subscribers Gained Per Video">
      <data key="d0">Subscribers Gained Per Video</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Subscribers Gained Per Video is a metric that reflects long-term engagement and signals strong video performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-06ab9774b6e9aa0aeab7a13fdb038dbc</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:platform-algorithm-signals:youtube-for-future-expansion</data>
      <data key="d5">1778002889</data>
      <data key="d6" />
