    <node id="Curiosity Gap">
      <data key="d0">Curiosity Gap</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Curiosity Gap refers to the technique of teasing information to engage viewers and encourage them to seek closure by continuing to watch.&lt;SEP&gt;Curiosity Gap is a variant concept related to creating interest by posing a question but is less disciplined compared to Open Loop.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-860b31095f79179d4d612439410f152e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b17b37f44382daee9503ba67b0f71f3</data>
