      <data key="d0">Reel Framing</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Reel framing involves composing video shots using the Rule of Thirds to guide viewer attention effectively.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a184060d44406503c4befead6608fca</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:rule-of-thirds</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003047</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Grid">
      <data key="d0">Grid</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The grid is a layout framework used in the Rule of Thirds, consisting of a 3x3 division of the frame to enhance image composition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-2a184060d44406503c4befead6608fca</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:rule-of-thirds</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003047</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="F-Pattern Reading">
      <data key="d0">F-Pattern Reading</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">F-Pattern Reading describes a specific way the eye scans text-heavy images in an F shape to enhance readability.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56cd18f7b7433212ca21b7261585e92e</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:f-pattern-reading</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nielsen Norman Group">
      <data key="d0">Nielsen Norman Group</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Nielsen Norman Group is a research organization known for its studies on web reading behavior and eye-tracking findings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56cd18f7b7433212ca21b7261585e92e</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:f-pattern-reading</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Static Images">
      <data key="d0">Static Images</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Static images are visual formats where text is the primary content and may follow the F-pattern for better readability.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56cd18f7b7433212ca21b7261585e92e</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:f-pattern-reading</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Eye-Tracking Findings">
      <data key="d0">Eye-Tracking Findings</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Eye-tracking findings are research results that illustrate how the eye scans and processes visual information, particularly in reading behavior.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56cd18f7b7433212ca21b7261585e92e</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:f-pattern-reading</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Text-Heavy Images">
      <data key="d0">Text-Heavy Images</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Text-heavy images are visual formats featuring substantial amounts of text, which utilize specific reading strategies like the F-pattern for improved comprehension.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56cd18f7b7433212ca21b7261585e92e</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:f-pattern-reading</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="IGTV">
      <data key="d0">IGTV</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">IGTV is a feature on Instagram that allows users to upload and view long-form videos in a vertical format.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c676dbaddd0ab5a88338a4bf4ae4f4c9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:mobile-first-9-16</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="YouTube Shorts">
      <data key="d0">YouTube Shorts</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">YouTube Shorts is a short video format on YouTube that supports vertical videos similar to TikTok.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c676dbaddd0ab5a88338a4bf4ae4f4c9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:mobile-first-9-16</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Vertical Video">
      <data key="d0">Vertical Video</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Vertical Video refers to videos designed in a 9:16 aspect ratio which achieve higher engagement on mobile platforms compared to horizontal formats.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c676dbaddd0ab5a88338a4bf4ae4f4c9</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:mobile-first-9-16</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003071</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Square (1:1) Format">
      <data key="d0">Square (1:1) Format</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Square (1:1) format refers to the default aspect ratio for posts on Instagram and Facebook feed.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-517177c19500ba4749eba4fa06e11417</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:square-1-1-for-feed</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003085</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Portrait (4:5) Format">
      <data key="d0">Portrait (4:5) Format</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Portrait (4:5) format is an aspect ratio that is used for mobile feed posts and takes up more vertical space than square.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-517177c19500ba4749eba4fa06e11417</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:square-1-1-for-feed</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003085</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Carousel Slides">
      <data key="d0">Carousel Slides</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Carousel slides are a feature on Instagram and Facebook that allows multiple images or videos to be displayed in a single post.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-517177c19500ba4749eba4fa06e11417</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:square-1-1-for-feed</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003085</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="1080×1080">
      <data key="d0">1080×1080</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">1080×1080 is the recommended resolution for square posts on social media platforms to maximize feed real estate.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-517177c19500ba4749eba4fa06e11417</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:square-1-1-for-feed</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003085</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="1080×1350">
      <data key="d0">1080×1350</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">1080×1350 is the recommended resolution for portrait (4:5) posts on social media platforms to maximize feed real estate.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-517177c19500ba4749eba4fa06e11417</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:square-1-1-for-feed</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003085</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Text Overlay Rules">
      <data key="d0">Text Overlay Rules</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Text Overlay Rules define guidelines to ensure text on images or videos is readable quickly on small screens.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reel Cover Text">
      <data key="d0">Reel Cover Text</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Reel Cover Text is described as an instance where overlaid text is used, adhering to specific readability standards.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Carousel Slide Headlines">
      <data key="d0">Carousel Slide Headlines</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Carousel Slide Headlines refer to headlines on carousel slides that must follow readability guidelines.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Image with Overlaid Copy">
      <data key="d0">Image with Overlaid Copy</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">An Image with Overlaid Copy is any image that contains text overlaid and must meet the readability criteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tactics">
      <data key="d0">Tactics</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tactics refer to specific strategies and methods recommended for effectively using text overlays on images and videos.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Size">
      <data key="d0">Size</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Size specifies the minimum font size for text overlays, indicating at least 60pt for reel covers and 80pt for carousel slides, tested at specific dimensions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Placement">
      <data key="d0">Placement</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Placement indicates recommended positioning for text overlays, suggesting top-left or center placement to avoid overlap with UI elements.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Length">
      <data key="d0">Length</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Length defines the maximum number of words per line for readability, allowing a maximum of 6-8 words per line and two lines for reel covers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Font">
      <data key="d0">Font</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Font emphasizes the use of sans-serif fonts for digital displays and the avoidance of thin weights that may not be visible at smaller sizes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f6564aff0f66e7c912366525fe36de3f</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:text-overlay-rules</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003102</data>
      <data key="d6" />
