    <node id="Dominant Color">
      <data key="d0">Dominant Color</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dominant Color is the primary color used in design that takes up the majority of the space in a composition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4fea7d7f065b62f47a9e8d0484fe5cae</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:brand-color-discipline</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003120</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Accent Color">
      <data key="d0">Accent Color</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Accent Color is the color used to complement the dominant color, creating visual interest and contrast in designs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4fea7d7f065b62f47a9e8d0484fe5cae</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:brand-color-discipline</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003120</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Highlight Color">
      <data key="d0">Highlight Color</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Highlight Color is the color that is used in the smallest proportion in a design, providing emphasis and drawing attention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4fea7d7f065b62f47a9e8d0484fe5cae</data>
      <data key="d4">knowledge:visual-design:brand-color-discipline</data>
      <data key="d5">1778003120</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Font Pairing">
      <data key="d0">Font Pairing</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Font Pairing refers to the practice of selecting one display font for headlines and one body font for other text elements.</data>
